      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six powerplant. This driver-focused example is equipped with a 6-speed manual transaxle and the factory M030 sport suspension package. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been addressed with an LN Engineering ceramic retrofit, and the rear main seal (RMS) remains dry. The cooling system has been proactively overhauled with a low-temp thermostat and a high-flow water pump to prevent bore scoring. While the finish shows minor road rash consistent with its 'good' condition status, the chassis dynamics are sharp thanks to updated Bilstein B6 dampers and refreshed control arm bushings. The G96/01 gearbox offers crisp gate engagement with no synchro hesitation. A technically sound, high-performance 911 ready for immediate spirited use.",
